An awaitable is any type that can be used with `co_await`. It controls:
- Whether to suspend (`await_ready()`)
- What to do when suspending (`await_suspend()`)
- What value to produce when resuming (`await_resume()`)

**Awaitable Interface:**

```cpp
struct MyAwaitable {
